The paper deals with a marketplace platform that mediates economic transactions between buyers and sellers, which falls under the category of game theory (cs.GT). The formulation of facility location problems involves the use of metric spaces and distance constraints, which are typical topics in data structures (cs.DS). The optimization of social surplus and profit using an LP rounding framework is a common theme in machine learning (cs.LG) and mathematical optimization (cs.MA). Finally, the use of stochastic processes and queueing analysis to model a dynamic marketplace setting is a topic in artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
